[{"id":"VR834472","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three charged particles each of charge positive uppercase Q in a vertical line. The charged particles are separated from each other by a distance D. A point charge of charge positive lowercase q is a distance D to the right of the middle particle of charge positive uppercase Q.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR834472.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three identical particles, each with the same charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive uppercase Q\"><math alttext=\"positive uppercase Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span>, are arranged in a vertical line with a spacing <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>D</mi></math></span></span> between adjacent particles, as shown in the figure. What is the net electrostatic force exerted on a point charge of charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive lowercase q\"><math alttext=\"positive lowercase q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> located the same distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>D</mi></math></span></span> to the right of the middle particle?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR834472_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"k times the fraction with numerator lowercase q times uppercase Q, and denominator D squared\"><math alttext=\"k times the fraction with numerator lowercase q times uppercase Q, and denominator D squared\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>k</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><msup><mi>D</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mf